[30;1m458 | [0m[35mtimeout is met. However, unlike {meth}`wait`, {meth}`get` will raise a {exc}`TimeoutError` if[0m
[30;1m459 | [0m[35mthe timeout is reached and the result is still not ready. If the result arrives before the[0m
[30;1m460 | [0m[35mtimeout is reached, then {meth}`get` will return the result itself if no exception was raised,[0m
[30;1m461 | [0m[35mand will raise an exception if there was.[0m

[30;1m447 | [0m[35mreturn whether the AR is done. You can also wait on an AsyncResult with its {meth}`wait` method.[0m
[30;1m448 | [0m[35mThis method blocks until the result arrives. If you don't want to wait forever, you can pass a[0m

[30;1m452 | [0m[35m{meth}`ready` and {meth}`wait` are insensitive to the success or failure of the call. After a[0m

[30;1m531 | [0m[35mso the Client.results cache should no longer grow unbounded.[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1502[0m[34m of [0m[33m2344[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m116 | [0m[35mwhich is necessary for building dependencies, it is critical that we don't submit any jobs[0m
[30;1m117 | [0m[35mbefore other jobs it may depend on. Fortunately, NetworkX provides a[0m
[30;1m118 | [0m[35m{meth}`topological_sort` method which ensures exactly this. It presents an iterable, that[0m
[30;1m119 | [0m[35mguarantees that when you arrive at a node, you have already visited all the nodes on which[0m
[30;1m120 | [0m[35mit depends:[0m
[30;1m121 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m122 | [0m[35m```ipython[0m

[30;1m11 | [0m[35m## Why are DAGs good for task dependencies?[0m
[30;1m12 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m13 | [0m[35mThe 'G' in DAG is 'Graph'. A Graph is a collection of **nodes** and **edges** that connect[0m
[30;1m14 | [0m[35mthe nodes. For our purposes, each node would be a task, and each edge would be a[0m
[30;1m15 | [0m[35mdependency. The 'D' in DAG stands for 'Directed'. This means that each edge has a[0m
[30;1m16 | [0m[35mdirection associated with it. So we can interpret the edge (a,b) as meaning that b depends[0m
[30;1m17 | [0m[35mon a, whereas the edge (b,a) would mean a depends on b. The 'A' is 'Acyclic', meaning that[0m

[30;1m411 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m412 | [0m[35m### Split Sends[0m
[30;1m413 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m414 | [0m[35mPreviously, messages were bundled as a single json object and one call to[0m
[30;1m415 | [0m[35m{func}`socket.send_json`. Since the hub inspects all messages, and doesn't need to[0m
[30;1m416 | [0m[35msee the content of the messages, which can be large, messages are now serialized and sent in[0m
[30;1m417 | [0m[35mpieces. All messages are sent in at least 4 parts: the header, the parent header, the metadata and t[0m
[30;1m418 | [0m[35mThis allows the controller to unpack and inspect the (always small) header,[0m
[30;1m419 | [0m[35mwithout spending time unpacking the content unless the message is bound for the[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1523[0m[34m of [0m[33m2344[0m[31m ]--[0m

[30;1m341 | [0m[35m## Control Messages[0m
[30;1m342 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m343 | [0m[35mMessages that interact with the engines, but are not meant to execute code, are submitted[0m
[30;1m344 | [0m[35mvia the Control queue. These messages have high priority, and are thus received and[0m
[30;1m345 | [0m[35mhandled before any execution requests.[0m

[30;1m81 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m82 | [0m[35m### IPython controller[0m
[30;1m83 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m84 | [0m[35mThe IPython controller processes provide an interface for working with a set of engines.[0m
[30;1m85 | [0m[35mAt a general level, the controller is a collection of processes to which IPython engines[0m
[30;1m86 | [0m[35mand clients can connect. The controller is composed of a {class}`Hub` and a collection of[0m
[30;1m87 | [0m[35m{class}`Schedulers`. These Schedulers are typically run in separate processes on the[0m
[30;1m88 | [0m[35msame machine as the Hub.[0m

[31m--[ [0m[34mMatch #[0m[33m1540[0m[34m of [0m[33m2344[0m[31m ]--[0m
   Rule Id: [34mBD000600[0m
       Tag: [34mSecurity.Backdoor.LOLBAS.Windows[0m

  Filename: [33m/ipyparallel-9.0.1/docs/source/tutorial/intro.md[0m
   Pattern: [32m\s(advpack\.dll|appvlp|at|atbroker|bash|bginfo|bitsadmin|cdb|certutil|cl_invocation\.ps1|cl_mutexverifiers\.ps1|cmd|cmdkey|cmstp|comsvcs\.dll|control|csc|cscript|csi|devtoolslauncher|dfsvc|diskshadow|dnscmd|dnx|dotnet|dxcap|esentutl|eventvwr|excel|expand|extexport|extrac32|findstr|forfiles|ftp|gfxdownloadwrapper|gpscript|hh|ie4uinit|ieadvpack\.dll|ieaframe\.dll|ic|infdefaultinstall|installutil|jsc|makecab|manage-bde\.wsf|mavinject|mftrace|microsoft\.workflow\.compiler|mmc|msbuild|msconfig|msdeploy|msdt|mshta|mshtml\.dll|msc|msxsl|netsh|odbcconf|pcalua|pcwrun|pcwutl\.dll|pester\.bat|powerpnt|presentationhost|pubprn\.vbs|rcsi|reg|regasm|regedit|register-cimprovider|regsvcs|regsvr32|rpcping|rundll32|runonce|runscripthelper|sc|schtasks|scriptrunner|setupapi\.dll|shdocvw\.dll|shell32\.dll|slmgr\.vbs|sqldumper|sqlps|sqltoolsps|squirrel|syncappvpublishingserver|syncappvpublishingserver\.vbs|syssetup\.dll|te|tracker|tttracer|update|url\.dll|verclsid|vsjitdebugger|wab|winrm\.vbs|winword|wmic|wscript|wsl|wsreset|xwizard|zipfldr\.dll)\s[0m
[30;1m45 | [0m[35m  local IPython session for plotting and analysis.[0m
[30;1m46 | [0m[35m- Run a set of tasks on a set of CPUs using dynamic load balancing.[0m

[30;1m151 | [0m[35m#### @ipp.depend[0m
[30;1m152 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m153 | [0m[35mThe `@ipp.depend` decorator lets you decorate any function with any _other_ function to[0m
[30;1m154 | [0m[35mevaluate the dependency. The dependency function will be called at the start of the task,[0m
[30;1m155 | [0m[35mand if it returns `False`, then the dependency will be considered unmet, and the task[0m
[30;1m156 | [0m[35mwill be assigned to another engine. If the dependency returns _anything other than[0m
[30;1m157 | [0m[35m`False`_, the rest of the task will continue.[0m

[30;1m350 | [0m[35m### Starting a cluster with SSH[0m
[30;1m351 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m352 | [0m[35mThe SSH mode uses {command}`ssh` to execute {command}`ipengine` on remote[0m
